58, 59, 60, 61 ...

754
01:05:23,700 --> 01:05:27,067
62, 63, 64.

755
01:05:43,119 --> 01:05:45,610
Well, he'll just have to compensate.

756
01:05:55,898 --> 01:05:57,798
[ Grunts ]

757
01:05:57,934 --> 01:06:01,495
All right. Could you hand me the--

758
01:06:03,873 --> 01:06:05,841
Thank you.

759
01:06:15,885 --> 01:06:20,219
<i>[ AJ.] Okay, / need everyone</i>

760
01:06:22,525 --> 01:06:25,358
- Whoa. What the--
- A.J.

761
01:06:25,461 --> 01:06:27,190
Someone's stealing water.

762
01:06:29,899 --> 01:06:32,800
I've had a suspicion
for the last few days...

763
01:06:32,935 --> 01:06:35,529
so I've been checking the levels.

764
01:06:38,107 --> 01:06:39,734
We don't need a gun.

765
01:06:39,842 --> 01:06:42,504
- [ Pistol Cocks ]
- A.J.

766
01:06:44,881 --> 01:06:48,112
You planning on
shooting someone, A.J.?

767
01:06:50,753 --> 01:06:53,153
While you've all been sleeping...

768
01:06:53,256 --> 01:06:55,224
I've been working.

769
01:06:57,360 --> 01:06:59,760
And, therefore,
I require more water.

770
01:06:59,862 --> 01:07:03,093
- Are you kidding me?
- Why didn't you just ask?

771
01:07:03,199 --> 01:07:07,135
Because I'm in charge
of building my plane...

772
01:07:07,236 --> 01:07:09,670
and I don't need to
ask anyone anything.

773
01:07:09,772 --> 01:07:12,240
We could all die of thirst!

774
01:07:13,376 --> 01:07:16,004
You need me, Towns.

775
01:07:16,112 --> 01:07:18,103
Don't forget that.

776
01:07:18,214 --> 01:07:20,341
You need me.

777
01:07:20,450 --> 01:07:23,510
Everyone here is dispensable
except me.

778
01:07:36,799 --> 01:07:38,790
[ Chuckling ]

779
01:07:52,782 --> 01:07:54,750
[ Exhales ]

780
01:07:56,853 --> 01:07:59,879
<i>[ Two Mortars Fire ]</i>

781
01:08:10,767 --> 01:08:13,031
[ Panting ]

782
01:08:33,990 --> 01:08:35,787
<i>[ Rady ]</i>
<i>They aren't nomads.</i>

783
01:08:35,892 --> 01:08:37,792
<i>[ AJ.]</i>
<i>How do you know?</i>

784
01:08:37,894 --> 01:08:39,862
<i>[ Rady ]</i>
<i>No women or children.</i>

785
01:08:46,402 --> 01:08:49,860
Smugglers or arms dealers.
Either way, it's bad news.

786
01:08:50,006 --> 01:08:51,906
<i>[ Rodney ]</i>
<i>But they could help us.</i>

787
01:08:52,008 --> 01:08:55,409
They could have water.
Maybe we could bargain with them.

788
01:08:55,511 --> 01:08:57,411
What do you think?

789
01:08:57,513 --> 01:09:00,243
- Should we go over there and find out?
- Whatever you wanna do, Frank.

790
01:09:00,349 --> 01:09:03,477
<i>What are you doing?</i>
<i>You can't go over there.</i>

791
01:09:03,586 --> 01:09:06,714
We can't risk losing the pilot.

792
01:09:06,823 --> 01:09:09,223
Then I'll go. You cover me.

793
01:09:09,325 --> 01:09:11,725
Did you hear what I just said?

794
01:09:11,828 --> 01:09:13,728
We got this, Elliott.

795
01:09:13,830 --> 01:09:16,731
Ian, don't you think
you should go as well?

796
01:09:16,833 --> 01:09:19,324
- Why me?
- Because you know most of the local dialects.

797
01:09:19,435 --> 01:09:21,335
- You do?
- Hold on.

798
01:09:21,437 --> 01:09:25,771
He's had to. He's worked all over the Gobi
doing negotiations with local crews.

799
01:09:25,875 --> 01:09:28,867
It's gon' be cool, man.
I got your back.

800
01:09:28,978 --> 01:09:31,412
And who's gonna look after yours?

801
01:09:35,818 --> 01:09:37,786
All right then.

802
01:09:39,655 --> 01:09:41,623
- Good luck, Frank.
- Good luck.

803
01:10:04,480 --> 01:10:10,214
.'.'<i>[ Woman Singing</i>.'<i>Ballad ]</i>

804
01:10:37,847 --> 01:10:40,748
You know, Alex, I--

805
01:10:40,850 --> 01:10:42,875
I just want to say that...

806
01:10:42,985 --> 01:10:45,886
you know, when I moved you
to the back of the plane...

807
01:10:45,988 --> 01:10:49,082
that was stupid and wrong,
and I'm really, really sorry.

808
01:10:51,227 --> 01:10:53,718
