You are, Elliott.

962
01:23:00,055 --> 01:23:02,148
You're the boss of everybody.

963
01:23:03,458 --> 01:23:05,949
<i>Now, can we please...</i>

964
01:23:06,061 --> 01:23:08,291
finish the airplane?

965
01:23:10,399 --> 01:23:12,890
Please?

966
01:23:29,518 --> 01:23:31,486
Careful.

967
01:23:41,897 --> 01:23:45,799
Did you clean the sand out of the engine
and do your preflight, Mr. Towns?

968
01:23:45,934 --> 01:23:49,301
- Three times.
- Well, do it again.

969
01:24:13,161 --> 01:24:15,629
What the hell are they waitin' for?

970
01:24:17,833 --> 01:24:20,825
They're waiting for us
to be too weak to fight back.

971
01:24:49,564 --> 01:24:51,532
It's ready.

972
01:24:59,174 --> 01:25:01,005
<i>[Jeremy ]</i>
<i>Know what this looks like?</i>

973
01:25:01,109 --> 01:25:02,872
Like a plane.

974
01:25:02,978 --> 01:25:04,878
With wings and everything.

975
01:25:06,915 --> 01:25:08,644
Think it'll fly?

976
01:25:09,684 --> 01:25:12,380
I'll shit myself if it does.

977
01:25:14,256 --> 01:25:16,850
[ All Laughing ]

978
01:25:16,958 --> 01:25:19,051
Oh, it'll fly.

979
01:25:21,196 --> 01:25:23,164
It better.

980
01:25:47,389 --> 01:25:49,289
How you doing?

981
01:25:49,391 --> 01:25:52,292
[ Clears Throat ]
I'm thirsty, hungry and tired.

982
01:25:52,394 --> 01:25:54,794
And I gotta get that thing
up in the air.

983
01:25:54,896 --> 01:25:57,524
But otherwise,
I'm having a hell of a time.

984
01:25:57,632 --> 01:25:59,532
How about you?

985
01:25:59,668 --> 01:26:01,397
I'm laughing.

986
01:26:01,536 --> 01:26:04,835
All I have to do is sit back,
relax and enjoy the flight.

987
01:26:07,275 --> 01:26:09,743
You'll get us out of here.
I know you will.

988
01:26:14,716 --> 01:26:18,743
Um, Frank,
I wanted to ask you something.

989
01:26:18,854 --> 01:26:22,415
What did Alex say to you
just before he died?

990
01:26:23,925 --> 01:26:25,893
''Don't crash.''

991
01:26:30,765 --> 01:26:34,565
Take something only to cover yourselves
up with. Nothing more.

992
01:26:34,703 --> 01:26:38,230
Hey, where's the chart?
I want to tape it to the floor.

993
01:26:38,373 --> 01:26:40,967
It's in my bag right there.

994
01:26:49,551 --> 01:26:53,043
<i>/ need you to check these cables</i>
<i>one more time.</i>

995
01:26:57,859 --> 01:27:00,293
This the outfit you work for?

996
01:27:07,903 --> 01:27:09,803
This catalog.

997
01:27:09,905 --> 01:27:11,873
Yeah.

998
01:27:19,314 --> 01:27:21,111
These are models.

999
01:27:22,150 --> 01:27:25,119
Wh-- Where's the big stuff?

1000
01:27:28,657 --> 01:27:30,852
Uh, well...

1001
01:27:30,959 --> 01:27:32,859
<i>there's the, uh...</i>

1002
01:27:32,961 --> 01:27:34,861
Stealth Magnum.

1003
01:27:34,963 --> 01:27:37,591
I designed that one a few years ago.

1004
01:27:39,301 --> 01:27:41,166
The biggest we make...

1005
01:27:41,303 --> 01:27:43,203
would have to be the <i>Albatross.</i>

1006
01:27:43,305 --> 01:27:45,739
Horrible name.

1007
01:27:45,840 --> 01:27:48,832
It's a six-foot wingspan
parasol model.

1008
01:27:48,977 --> 01:27:54,005
But it's not my design because it's a glider,
and I only work on power models.

1009
01:27:54,115 --> 01:27:56,743
<i>But you design the big stuff too.</i>
<i>Right, Elliott?</i>

1010
01:27:56,851 --> 01:28:01,515
<i>Planes that carry people.</i>
<i>Planes like the</i> Phoenix. <i>Right?</i>

1011
01:28:04,025 --> 01:28:05,925
No, no.

1012
01:28:06,027 --> 01:28:08,996
Sizemore and Pratt
only build model airplanes.

1013
01:28:10,332 --> 01:28:14,268
But... that's who you design for.

1014
01:28:14,369 --> 01:28:16,701
I'm their chief designer, yes.

1015
01:28:18,840 --> 01:28:21,434
You build toy planes, man?

1016
01:28:21,543 --> 01:28:25,741
No, I most certainly
do not design toy planes.

1017
01:28:28,316 --> 01:28:32,412
<i>A toy plane is one of those balsa wood</i>
<i>creations that run on a rubber band.</i>

1018
01:28:32,520 --> 01:28:34,283
- Those are not toys.
- These are toys.

1019
01:28:34,389 --> 01:28:35,913
Those are not toys.

1020
01:28:36,024 --> 01:28:39,687
They're not full-sized aircraft either,
Elliott.

1021
01:28:39,794 --> 01:28:42,092
You see this shit?
He's a goddamn toy maker!

1022
01:28:42,197 --> 01:28:46,861
I think, Mr. Towns, you should appreciate
two very important things.

1023
01:28:47,002 --> 01:28:49,994
<i>First of all, precisely similar</i>
<i>principles of aerodynamics...</i>

1024
01:28:50,138 --> 01:28:53,198
<i>apply to both scale</i>
<i>and full-sized aircraft.</i>

1025
01:28:53,341 --> 01:28:56,777
- What is he saying?
- <i>We should have waited, man.</i>
<i>We'd still have water left.</i>

1026
01:28:56,911 --> 01:29:00,244
<i>Air foil surfaces,</i>

1027
01:29:00,348 --> 01:29:04,011
the whole pattern of heavier-than-air
construction are all precisely similar.

1028
01:29:04,119 --> 01:29:06,019
[ Mutters ]
We're gonna die out here.

1029
01:29:06,121 --> 01:29:09,557
<i>The second thing you should realize</i>
<i>is that a model plane has to fly itself.</i>

1030
01:29:09,658 --> 01:29:11,387
<i>There is no pilot.</i>

1031
01:29:11,493 --> 01:29:15,259
The design must be even more efficient
than that of a full-sized aircraft.

1032
01:29:15,363 --> 01:29:18,799
Well, I'm looking
through your catalog here...

1033
01:29:18,900 --> 01:29:23,030
and I don't see anything about
a flying sled with people on the wings!

1034
01:29:24,239 --> 01:29:26,139
They're toy airplanes!

1035
01:29:26,241 --> 01:29:28,334
What kind of crap is that?

1036
01:29:28,443 --> 01:29:30,809
My plane will fly.

1037
01:29:30,912 --> 01:29:34,643
You knew all along that you
was buildin' a toy airplane!

1038
01:29:41,356 --> 01:29:43,256
<i>[ Kelly ]</i>

1039
01:29:43,358 --> 01:29:45,258
<i>/an, what are you doing?</i>

1040
01:29:45,360 --> 01:29:49,023
[ Ian ] We'd have had two more weeks
if it weren't for you.

1041
01:29:50,865 --> 01:29:52,765
They could have found us.

1042
01:29:52,901 --> 01:29:55,802
- [ Echoing, Faint ] The plane will fly!

1043
01:29:55,904 --> 01:29:59,635
We should have listened to Towns
in the beginning.

1044
01:29:59,741 --> 01:30:02,676
Sit tight, save water,
and they'll find us.

1045
01:30:02,777 --> 01:30:04,972
- [ Echoing, Faint ] What are you doing?
- But no.

1046
01:30:05,080 --> 01:30:08,015
- You had to build your plane.

1047
01:30:08,116 --> 01:30:10,846
- And you're not even one of us.

1048
01:30:10,952 --> 01:30:13,819
- Ian! Put that gun down!

1049
01:30:13,922 --> 01:30:16,413
- Nobody's shooting anybody!

1050
01:30:16,524 --> 01:30:18,424
We're not going out like that!

1051
01:30:18,526 --> 01:30:20,517
- My plane will fly!
- Give me the gun!

1052
01:30:20,628 --> 01:30:24,428
No, no, I was just saying,
I'm a very important person to them.

1053
01:30:24,532 --> 01:30:27,990
- Ian!
- They're looking for me.
All they needed was more time.

1054
01:30:29,671 --> 01:30:31,696
We just needed more time!

1055
01:30:31,840 --> 01:30:33,933
- We need time!

1056
01:30:34,075 --> 01:30:36,805
Give me the gun! Give me that gun!

1057
01:30:36,911 --> 01:30:39,141
- Come on.

1058
01:30:39,247 --> 01:30:41,147
[ Sobbing ]

1059
01:30:43,251 --> 01:30:46,152
<i>[ Creaking ]</i>

1060
01:30:46,254 --> 01:30:50,054
Everyone, look! Look!

1061
01:30:56,998 --> 01:30:59,831
Holy shit.

1062
01:31:08,176 --> 01:31:10,144
I told you.

1063
01:31:11,813 --> 01:31:13,781
I told you.

1064
01:31:14,916 --> 01:31:17,749
We have to get inside!

1065
01:31:20,321 --> 01:31:23,347
Inside! Get inside!

1066
01:31:35,570 --> 01:31:37,970
<i>All the weight's on the</i> Phoenix!

1067
01:31:38,072 --> 01:31:39,869
[ All Screaming ]

1068
01:32:03,464 --> 01:32:06,092
[ Sammi ]
I can't believe it.

1069
01:32:06,234 --> 01:32:08,202
We build a plane...

1070
01:32:09,838 --> 01:32:12,807
we can't even fly it out of here.

1071
01:32:13,908 --> 01:32:15,637
All that sand...

1072
01:32:15,743 --> 01:32:17,711
it's probably not even gonna start.

1073
01:32:18,880 --> 01:32:20,848
It'll start.

1074
01:32:29,224 --> 01:32:31,124
Listen.

1075
01:32:31,226 --> 01:32:33,194
We built this plane.

1076
01:32:35,730 --> 01:32:38,324
With our own hands we built it.

1077
01:32:39,701 --> 01:32:42,295
We can sure as hell dig it out.

1078
01:32:49,210 --> 01:32:51,178
Did you hear what I said?

1079
01:32:53,181 --> 01:32:55,149
We built it.

1080
01:32:58,853 --> 01:33:00,753
<i>We're not garbage.</i>

1081
01:33:01,956 --> 01:33:04,356
We're people...

1082
01:33:04,459 --> 01:33:06,427
with families...

1083
01:33:07,795 --> 01:33:10,286
and lives to live.

1084
01:33:13,167 --> 01:33:15,135
<i>All of us.</i>

1085
01:33:21,042 --> 01:33:23,272
I don't wanna die like this.

1086
01:33:27,015 --> 01:33:28,915
Come on.

1087
01:33:29,017 --> 01:33:31,417
Let's get the hell out of here.

1088
01:33:34,956 --> 01:33:36,719
Let's go home.

1089
01:34:01,182 --> 01:34:03,844
[ All Grunting ]

1090
01:34:09,691 --> 01:34:12,251
[ Kelly ]
Come on!

1091
01:34:13,561 --> 01:34:16,291
[ A.J. ]
Come on! Get up!

1092
01:34:18,933 --> 01:34:21,265
Come on. Come on!

1093
01:34:21,402 --> 01:34:23,996
- [ Groans ]
- [ Grunting ]

1094
01:34:37,318 --> 01:34:39,445
<i>[ Frank ]</i>
<i>All right, that's far enough.</i>

1095
01:34:59,707 --> 01:35:01,641
It's kinda beautiful, isn't it?

1096
01:35:01,776 --> 01:35:04,404
Don't tell us you wanna stick around.

1097
01:35:04,512 --> 01:35:07,106
Not with you, I don't.

1098
01:35:09,350 --> 01:35:11,409
[ Chuckles ]

1099
01:35:11,519 --> 01:35:13,612
Whatever happens now...

1100
01:35:15,623 --> 01:35:18,148
we did something
pretty amazing here.

1101
01:35:19,494 --> 01:35:21,962
- Yes, we did, didn't we?
- [ Laughs ]

1102
01:35:23,498 --> 01:35:25,466
Good luck.

1103
01:35:27,001 --> 01:35:28,764
<i>Uh...</i>

1104
01:35:29,837 --> 01:35:32,431
Captain Towns...

1105
01:35:35,009 --> 01:35:36,977
we only have, uh...

1106
01:35:37,078 --> 01:35:39,740
five chances at this, so, uh...

1107
01:35:41,849 --> 01:35:44,249
good luck.

1108
01:36:02,837 --> 01:36:04,805
Okay.

1109
01:36:14,148 --> 01:36:16,048
Hey, Frank...

1110
01:36:16,150 --> 01:36:18,550
I want you to borrow this.

1111
01:36:18,653 --> 01:36:21,451
It's always been good luck for me.

1112
01:36:23,658 --> 01:36:25,626
Who needs luck?

1113
01:37:35,863 --> 01:37:38,127
Clear.

1114
01:37:41,802 --> 01:37:43,827
[ Cartridge Fires ]

1115
01:37:45,573 --> 01:37:48,041
<i>[ Explosion Reverberating ]</i>

1116
01:37:56,951 --> 01:37:59,351
<i>[ Cartridge Fires ]</i>

1117
01:38:00,555 --> 01:38:03,718
[ Turbine Whining, Chugging ]

1118
01:38:03,824 --> 01:38:05,621
Come on, baby. Come on.

1119
01:38:08,362 --> 01:38:10,830
Come on!

1120
01:38:13,534 --> 01:38:16,662
- Come on.
- [ Engine Shutting Down ]

1121
01:38:29,650 --> 01:38:31,618
<i>[ Cartridge Fires ]</i>

1122
01:38:31,719 --> 01:38:34,449
[ Turbine Whining, Chugging ]

1123
01:38:35,756 --> 01:38:38,452
- Come on.
- Come on.

1124
01:38:38,559 --> 01:38:41,824
- Turn over.

1125
01:38:43,097 --> 01:38:45,065
- [ Engine Chugging, Shutting Down ]
- Please!

1126
01:38:48,769 --> 01:38:50,532
Come on!

1127
01:38:56,143 --> 01:38:58,373
[ Mutters ]
Shit.

1128
01:39:05,519 --> 01:39:08,420
I'm gonna fire the next cartridge
with the ignition off...

1129
01:39:08,522 --> 01:39:10,490
to clear the cylinders.

1130
01:39:12,893 --> 01:39:16,351
But, Captain Towns,
there are only two left!

1131
01:39:16,464 --> 01:39:18,398
I know.

1132
01:39:19,467 --> 01:39:21,662
But I--
[ Sighs ]

1133
01:39:23,938 --> 01:39:25,769
[ Sighs ]

1134
01:39:25,873 --> 01:39:28,341
- <i>[ Switch Clicks ]</i>
- <i>[ Gun Cylinder Rotates ]</i>

1135
01:39:41,355 --> 01:39:43,585
-<i>[ Cartridge Fires ]</i>
- Oh, shit!

1136
01:39:45,159 --> 01:39:47,457
-Jesus!
- [ Groans ]

1137
01:39:54,802 --> 01:39:56,770
Okay.

1138
01:39:58,306 --> 01:40:00,274
[ Whispers ]
Come on.

1139
01:40:04,178 --> 01:40:05,645
[ Cartridge Fires ]

1140
01:40:05,746 --> 01:40:09,147
- [ Turbine Whining, Chugging ]
- Come on, baby.

1141
01:40:11,786 --> 01:40:14,812
- Come on.

1142
01:40:14,922 --> 01:40:17,584
- Come on!
- Come on!

1143
01:40:20,461 --> 01:40:22,827
Come on, baby!

1144
01:40:23,898 --> 01:40:27,163
- Come on!
- <i>[ Engine Racing ]</i>

1145
01:40:27,301 --> 01:40:30,031
- Yes!
- Yes, yes, yes!

1146
01:40:30,171 --> 01:40:32,071
Ohh!

1147
01:40:32,173 --> 01:40:34,073
<i>[ All Shouting ]</i>

1148
01:40:37,878 --> 01:40:39,903
<i>[ AJ.]</i>

1149
01:40:40,014 --> 01:40:43,745
- Yeah!
- Yes! We make our own luck!

1150
01:40:43,851 --> 01:40:45,375
- Yes! Yes!
- Come on!

1151
01:40:45,486 --> 01:40:47,044
Yeah!

1152
01:40:47,154 --> 01:40:49,054
[ Laughing ]

1153
01:40:49,156 --> 01:40:52,319
- Yes! Yes!
- [ Laughing Continues ]

1154
01:40:52,426 --> 01:40:55,918
Everybody! Up!

1155
01:40:56,030 --> 01:40:59,022
Let's go home! Come on!

1156
01:40:59,133 --> 01:41:02,227
- Yeah!
- Come on! Let's go!

1157
01:41:02,370 --> 01:41:04,600
We're going home!

1158
01:41:16,150 --> 01:41:18,050
One for the lucky man!

1159
01:41:18,152 --> 01:41:20,211
[ Laughing ]

1160
01:41:23,023 --> 01:41:24,991
Thank you.

1161
01:41:49,650 --> 01:41:51,880
Mr. Towns!

1162
01:41:51,986 --> 01:41:54,386
[ All Shouting ]

1163
01:41:56,557 --> 01:41:58,684
Hang on!

1164
01:42:29,023 --> 01:42:32,823
- Towns, we have a problem!
- Elliott, where's my rudder? I've lost my rudder!

1165
01:42:32,927 --> 01:42:37,387
- That's what I'm trying to tell you!
- Well, stop talking and fix it!

1166
01:42:41,101 --> 01:42:42,932
Shit.

1167
01:42:54,582 --> 01:42:57,312
[ Grunting ]

1168
01:43:03,824 --> 01:43:05,724
[ Gunfire Continues ]

1169
01:43:07,628 --> 01:43:09,596
Aah!

1170
01:43:21,976 --> 01:43:25,173
Towns, get us outta here!
This shit ain't funny no more!

1171
01:43:40,261 --> 01:43:42,627
Here we go!

1172
01:43:45,132 --> 01:43:47,566
[ Shouting ]

1173
01:44:09,323 --> 01:44:12,554
[ Cheering, Whooping ]

1174
01:44:12,660 --> 01:44:14,560
Yeah!

1175
01:44:14,662 --> 01:44:16,630
Hey, boy!

1176
01:44:20,434 --> 01:44:22,459
Yeah!

1177
01:44:22,603 --> 01:44:25,333
[ Cheering, Shouting ]

1178
01:44:25,472 --> 01:44:28,168
We're flying! Yes!

1179
01:44:29,443 --> 01:44:31,343
Yes!

1180
01:44:31,445 --> 01:44:33,208
Whoo-hoo!

1181
01:44:39,753 --> 01:44:42,586
Yeah! Yeah!

1182
01:44:42,690 --> 01:44:47,059
<i>[ Sammi ]</i>

1183
01:45:23,097 --> 01:45:26,032
.'.'<i>[ Rock ]</i>

1184
01:45:58,732 --> 01:46:02,133
.'.'<i>[ Man Singing</i>.'<i>Rock ]</i>

1185
01:47:09,436 --> 01:47:12,564
.'.'<i>[ Continues ]</i>

1186
01:48:12,332 --> 01:48:15,529
.'.'<i>[ Ends ]</i>

1187
01:52:40,467 --> 01:52:45,370
<i>[ Airplane Passing ]</i>

